case.name: Bahonko v Nurses Board of Australia [2007] FCA 71 (1 February 2007)

citphrases.citphrase: referral by county court of victoria to victorian civil and administrative tribunal ('vcat') of issue whether a guardian or an administrator should be appointed for the applicant
whether stay should be granted pending outcome of determination of vcat

citances.sentence: 25 On 1 February 2007, Heerey J heard argument seeking leave to appeal the decision of the Court given on 20 December 2006, and dismissed the application with costs: Bahonko v Nurses Board of Victoria [2007] FCA 71. I have been informed by senior counsel for the first respondent that on 21 February 2007 the applicant has sought special leave to appeal in the High Court of Australia the decision of Heerey J.
